<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 2:39PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Washington and southeastern Iron Counties through 315 PM MDT...
At 238 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northwest of Zion National Park, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Zion National Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to localized flooding including in slot canyons. Do not drive your
vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
